    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Knives with a gauge or other contrivance on the blade to limit the depth of the cut or the amount cut off. Such knives are most often used for leatherworking, but may be used in other contexts as well, such as in paper production, in the kitchen, and elsewhere.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
